        "layout": "balanced-layout",
        "layoutData": {
          "leftPanel": {
            "title": "Bitcoin's Wild Ride",
            "paragraphs": [
              "<strong>2017:</strong> $1K \u2192 $19K <span style=\"color: green;\">(+1,800%)</span>",
              "<strong>2018:</strong> $19K \u2192 $3.2K <span style=\"color: red;\">(-83%)</span>",
              "<strong>2021:</strong> $10K \u2192 $69K <span style=\"color: green;\">(+590%)</span>",
              "<strong>2022:</strong> $47K \u2192 $16K <span style=\"color: red;\">(-66%)</span>",
              "<strong>2024:</strong> $16K \u2192 $63K <span style=\"color: green;\">(+280%)</span>"
            ]
          },
          "rightPanel": {
            "stats": [],
            "infoCard": {
              "title": "Critical Risks",
              "color": "rose",
              "items": [
                "\u26a0\ufe0f Extreme volatility (10-20% daily swings)",
                "\u26a0\ufe0f Regulatory uncertainty worldwide",
                "\u26a0\ufe0f Exchange hacks (billions stolen)",
                "\u26a0\ufe0f Permanent loss if you lose passwords",
                "\u26a0\ufe0f Less regulated = manipulation risk",
                "",
                "<strong>Recommendation:</strong> 1-5% maximum\u2014only money you can afford to lose COMPLETELY"
              ]
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "number": 12,
      "type": "content",
      "headerColor": "amber",
      "content": {
        "headerTitle": "\ud83c\udfd7\ufe0f Foundation First Principle",
        "layout": "concept-full",
        "layoutData": {
          "title": "Build your financial foundation BEFORE exploring alternatives",
          "paragraphs": [
            "<strong>The Wealth Pyramid (Bottom to Top):</strong>",
            "",
            "<strong>Level 1 (Base):</strong> Emergency Fund (3-6 months expenses)",
            "<strong>Level 2:</strong> Retirement Contributions (401k/Roth IRA)",
            "<strong>Level 3:</strong> Taxable Investment Account (Index Funds)",
            "<strong>Level 4 (Top):</strong> Alternative Investments (10-20% max after foundation)"
          ],
          "keyPoint": "\"Stocks and bonds are vegetables and protein. Alternatives are dessert. You need the foundation first.\""
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "number": 13,
      "type": "content",
      "headerColor": "rose",
      "content": {
        "headerTitle": "\ud83d\udea9 Red Flags to Watch For",
        "layout": "comparison-grid",
        "layoutData": {
          "leftColumn": {
            "icon": "\ud83d\udea8",
            "title": "\"Guaranteed Returns\"",
            "items": [
              "No legitimate investment guarantees returns. This phrase almost always signals a SCAM.",
              "",
              "<strong>Reality:</strong> All investments carry risk. Higher promised returns = higher risk."
            ]
          },
          "centerColumn": {
            "icon": "\u26a1",
            "title": "\"Everyone's Getting Rich\"",
            "items": [
              "When everyone is talking about an investment, you're probably late to the party.",
              "",
              "<strong>Reality:</strong> By the time it's mainstream news, smart money has often already exited."
            ]
          },
          "rightColumn": {
            "icon": "\ud83d\ude30",
            "title": "\"You'll Regret Missing Out\"",
            "items": [
              "FOMO (fear of missing out) is a terrible basis for investment decisions.",
              "",
              "<strong>Reality:</strong> Good investments don't require urgency tactics."
            ]
          }
        }
      }
    },
    {
